                     Amercement.And ſhall incur ſuch Fine as the ſame Iuſtice ſhall think fit to Impoſe on ſuch Officer, not excéeding the Sum of xl s. for any one Offence;
                        N. 4. the ſame Fine to be Levied by the High Conſtable of ſuch Place or Diviſion, or any other Officer by Warrant under the Hand and Seal of ſuch Iuſtice of the Peace upon the Goods and Chattels of the Perſon ſo offending, rendring the overplus to the owner thereof, all neceſſary Charges in Levying the ſame being firſt deducted, to be Imployed for the Amending of the High-wayes of the Pariſh


or Place where ſuch neglect ſhall be found, as the ſaid Iuſtice or Iuſtices ſhall appoint for the doing thereof.

